deck: Strong-arm gangster lieutenant to Lorenzo Valenti.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Johnny Palumbo is a tough-guy assistant to Lorenzo Valenti, one of the five main gangs in New York in the Shadow's universe, as portrayed in the Grendel vs the Shadow crossover.

Johnny is Lorenzo's right-hand man and helps him run the family's business. He also watches out for Lorenzo's daughter, Sofia, and her friend, Frannie, whose boyfriend is abusive.

Johnny is very unhappy when Grendel (Hunter Rose) arrives in town and starts taking over all the organized crime in the city, starting with the Valentis. He and Lorenzo believe they are being disrespected. At one point he draws a gun on Hunter, who only lets him survive out as a sign of respect to Lorenzo. However they do appreciate the extra money that Grendel makes for the mobs. Sofia starts to romance and seduce Rose.

Eventually Sofia manipulates Lorenzo into trying to kill Grendel, and then she kills her father using Grendel's fork. However she then reveals that she has been secret lovers with Johnny the whole time, and they plan to frame Grendel for Lorenzo's death. Hunter is conflicted by his love for Sofia but is about to kill her when Johnny shoots Grendel. He may have shot him in the back, and when he was stunned by Sofia's betrayal, but it is still one of the only times Grendel has been wounded by anyone.

The scene is interrupted by the Shadow, and he and Grendel run off during the battle, presumably leaving Johnny and Sofia still in charge of the Valenti gang.

Johnny's last name is only revealed at the end of the series. This is the same last name as Grendel's adopted daughter, Stacy Palumbo. It is possible that, at least in the Shadow universe and potentially also in the Grendel universe, Johnny and Sofia have children, one of which is either Barry Palumbo, Stacy's uncle, or Stacy Palumbo's parents. This would make Johnny and Sofia either the direct or indirect ancestors of Barry, Stacy, and Christine Spar, and thus important progenitors of the Grendel legacy. (However, since Hunter and Sofia slept together on multiple occasions, it is also possible that her potential children would actually be Hunter's, not Johnny's, even if they were given Johnny's last name.)
name: Johnny Palumbo

deck: Daughter of a crime boss with ambitions of her own, and one of the few lovers of Hunter Rose.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Sofia is the daughter of Lorenzo Valenti, leader of one of the five main gangs in New York in the Shadow's universe, as portrayed in the Grendel vs the Shadow crossover. Sofia, a strikingly beautiful and intelligent woman who is also extremely ambitious, and feels that her father's management of the mob could be more expansive. She often consorts with one of Lorenzo's lieutenants, Johnny Palumbo, who looks out for her and her friend Frannie.

Lorenzo is very unhappy when Grendel (Hunter Rose) arrives in town and starts taking over all the organized crime in the city, starting with the Valentis. He is old-school and believes they are being disrespected. He had also planned on taking over all the mobs himself, so Grendel is ruining his plans. Meanwhile, Sofia starts to romance Rose. She first runs into him in his civilian identity, and finds him charmingly arrogant. However she also meets him as Grendel and is attracted to his powerful demeanor in that guise as well.

Johnny tells her that Frannie was beaten to death by her abusive boyfriend. She tries to trap the boyfriend and kill him, but is discovered. Luckily Grendel comes in and saves her and kills the boyfriend. She and Grendel finally embrace, and she actually gets him to remove his mask and reveal his identity, which he does for very few people. Indeed, Rose is conflicted, for he had sworn never to love again after Jocasta, but he finds himself fully falling for Sofia, somewhat against his better judgement.

Eventually Sofia manipulates Lorenzo into trying to kill Grendel and take over all the mobs himself, at which point she kills her father using Grendel's fork. However she then reveals that she has been secret lovers with Johnny the whole time, and they plan to frame Grendel for Lorenzo's death so that she and Johnny can take over the gang. Grendel is stunned, because he prides himself on manipulating others, and can't believe he was manipulated himself. However, women have always been his blind spot, as is eventually seen by his adopted daughter Stacy's betrayal.

He is considering whether to kill Sofia when he is shot in the back by Johnny, and the Shadow soon intervenes, so he leaves. Sofia and Johnny presumably remain the leaders of the Valenti gang.

It turns out that Johnny shares the same last name as Grendel's adopted daughter, Stacy Palumbo. It is possible that, at least in the Shadow universe and potentially also in the Grendel universe, Johnny and Sofia have children, one of which is either Barry Palumbo, Stacy's uncle, or Stacy Palumbo's parents. It is also possible, since she slept with Rose on multiple occasions, that any children she had would be Hunter's, not Johnny's, even if they were given Johnny's last name. Either way, this would make Sofia either the direct or indirect ancestors of Barry, Stacy, and Christine Spar, and thus an important progenitor of the Grendel legacy.
name: Sofia Valenti

deck: An artist, Catwoman's one-time best friend/roommate.
description:
Storyline

An artist from Flagstaff, Arizona whom Selina Kyle befriended.

They became roommates and friends and Selina later relieved to her that she was Catwoman.

Shortly after that though, her and Selina's apparent got blown up by one of Selina's enemies while they were both in it.

Selena got her out alive, but when Arizona woke up in the hospital later, her memories were damaged.

Selina let her parents take her home and didn't contact her again, feeling guilty for what had happened to her becasue they were friends.

Information

  • Name: "Arizona" is a nickname, her real name is unknown. Selina would call her "Ari" sometimes though, while Arizona would, in turn, call Selina "Sel".
  • Place of Birth: Flagstaff, Arizona
  • Residence: She shared an apparent with Selina Kyle in the Brideshead neighborhood of Gotham City for a time, but has since returned home to Flagstaff with her parents.
  • Occupation: Artist (painter)
  • Hair Color: At first, her hair was shown to be blonde and straight, in subsequent appearances though, she changed it to orange-blond and curly.

description:
Ghost Writer, Jacob 'Jake' Stone is the lead character in Jazan Wild's Funhouse of Horrors Series.

Jacob 'Jake' Stone, while on a family picnic, stumbles upon an old, abandoned house in the woods just a week before Halloween. The wretched place is being prepared as a one-night-only haunted house. One of the workers, a strange man known only as Ole Scratch, sees Jacob 'Jake' Stone and gives him a book of ghost stories with two tickets inside. They forever change his life… or what's left of it, anyway, after the ghosts are done with him. And the ghosts are NEVER done with Jake. As he grows, so does the terror. Deciding that the ghouls and goblins are never going to take a hint, and leave him to rest in peace, Jake Stone decides to become a ghost writer. It would seem that the living impaired have a lot to say.
name: Jake Stone

description:
Esmeralda the Fortune Teller appears in Jazan Wild's Carnival of Souls comic series issues 1 through 3 and the Strongman comic. The soothsayer's back-story is told in issue 3 and also in a chapter in the Carnival of Souls novel.

Esmeralda's mother was burned at the stake, accused of being a witch for giving birth to a daughter who could hear the town's secrets. Her mother freed herself and Esmeralda from the ropes and commanded the young girl to run to the Carnival of Souls, which they had recently visited, and let the caravan take her away.

Esmeralda the Fortune Teller is mentioned in the second graphic novel in the Dandy series, "Step Into The Krazy Life", as well as in the Dandy Novel. Dandy gets a reading from Esmeralda and Jexter the Clown confirms that Dandy will not be joining the Freak Show but will rather be destined to another magical journey. A dandy one.
name: Esmeralda The Fortune Teller
